# ProductivOS — Core Rules

## Project Identity
Full-stack productivity app: FastAPI backend + React frontend + PostgreSQL via Supabase.
Spec file: PRODUCTIVOS_PROJECT_SPEC.md — read before any change.

## Absolute Constraints
- Python packages: uv only. NEVER suggest pip install.
- Database: Supabase Python client only. NEVER use SQLAlchemy.
- user_id placeholder: "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
- Do NOT add features beyond what is explicitly asked.
- Do NOT modify database schema.
- Do NOT refactor working code unless asked.

## Code Behavior
- Smallest possible change to achieve the goal.
- Always add error handling — no bare except, no unhandled rejections.
- Check existing code before writing new code to avoid duplication.
- One responsibility per file.
- Do not write comments unless logic is genuinely non-obvious.

## Response Behavior  
- Do not explain what you're about to do — just do it.
- Do not summarize what you just did — the diff speaks for itself.
- If the task is unclear, ask ONE question before writing code.
- Do not suggest improvements unless asked.
- Do not add TODOs or placeholder comments in delivered code.

## Running Commands
```bash
# Backend
cd backend && uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# Frontend
cd frontend && npm run dev
```
